 as an ephemeral kind of writing and illegible script occurring in space.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aChoreographie. 4aJan Fabre. 4aLiteratur. 4aMedienästhetik. 4aPerformance Studies. 4aPostmoderne. 4aSchriftphilosophie. 4aTrisha Brown. 4aVisual Studies. 4aWilliam Forsythe. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / General.2bisacsh  aChoreography.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aJan Fabre.  aLiterature.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aPerformance Studies.  aPhilosophy of Writing.  aPostmodernism.  aTrisha Brown.  aVisual Studies.  aWilliam Forsythe.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383763814140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839438145?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839438145423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839438145/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2022